  "pr_number": 2237,
  "issue_number": 2236,
  "issue_title": "Add Flutter theme foundation from Sure design tokens",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nAdd the first Flutter design-system foundation layer by deriving mobile theme values from Sure's canonical design tokens.\n\n## Problem\n\nThe Flutter app currently defines light and dark `ThemeData` inline in `mobile/lib/main.dart` using a Material seed color. That makes the mobile app easy to drift away from the web app's design-system tokens, especially as the design system continues to evolve around `design/tokens/sure.tokens.json`.\n\n## Proposed scope\n\n- Add a small generator that reads `design/tokens/sure.tokens.json`.\n- Generate typed Flutter token constants under `mobile/lib/theme/`.\n- Add a shared `SureTheme` for light and dark `ThemeData`.\n- Replace the duplicated inline `ThemeData` blocks in `mobile/lib/main.dart`.\n- Add focused tests for token generation and theme wiring.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- No full screen restyle.\n- No screenshot/mockup CSS copied into Dart.\n- No native font asset registration until mobile-ready font assets are available.\n- No redesign of navigation, forms, cards, dashboard, settings, or transaction screens in this issue.\n\n## Validation target\n\n- Generator check proves generated tokens are current.\n- Flutter analyze/test pass.\n- iOS simulator debug build passes.\n- Follow-up visible screen work can use the same token/theme foundation instead of inventing mobile-only palettes.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-11T14:19:15.000Z",
